Disk World creator help
query_room_at

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
query_room_at -  This method is used to find a room at the specified coordinates, if one has already been cloned.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
object query_room_at(int x,
int y,
int z)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^x%^RESET%^ - the x coordinate of the room (internal coordinate system)
%^BOLD%^y%^RESET%^ - the y coordinate of the room (internal coordinate system)
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
the room at those coordinates, or 0 if none has been cloned.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/room/inherit/terrain_map/handler_base.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method is used to find a room at the specified coordinates,
if one has already been cloned.
If a room has been cloned at those coordinates, it is returned,
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
load_room_at, query_room, query_rooms_in_block, query_rooms_in_range

.EP

